title: Print, "Our Watering Places - The Empty Sleeve at Newport", August 26, 1865
medium: Wood engraving printed in black ink on paper
provenance: Gift of Mrs. Cora E. Wilson
description: Horizontal view of a wicker trap containing a woman and man with military cap of the Northern United States at the time of the Civil War; his left coat is empty and pinned under his lapel.  Beach is visible in the distance, and the ocean beyond.
